name: r-pma

owner.description: Bioconda is a distribution of bioinformatics software realized as a channel for the versatile Conda package manager.
owner.name: bioconda

summary: Performs Penalized Multivariate Analysis: a penalized matrix decomposition, sparse principal components analysis, and sparse canonical correlation analysis, described in the following papers: (1) Witten, Tibshirani and Hastie (2009) A penalized matrix decomposition, with applications to sparse principal components and canonical correlation analysis. Biostatistics 10(3):515-534. (2) Witten and Tibshirani (2009) Extensions of sparse canonical correlation analysis, with applications to genomic data. Statistical Applications in Genetics and Molecular Biology 8(1): Article 28.
